1 2. “Covered entity” means an institution or facility operated
2 by the Department of Corrections or contracted with the Department
3 of Corrections as provided in Section 502 of Title 57 of the
4 Oklahoma Statutes;
5 3. “Multi-occupancy” means a space that is designed to be
6 utilized by multiple persons simultaneously;
7 4. “Restroom” means a room that includes one or more toilets or
8 urinals; and
9 5. “Sleeping quarters” means a room that contains a bed and in
10 which more than one individual is housed overnight.
11 B. 1. A covered entity shall designate each multi-occupancy
12 restroom, changing room, and sleeping quarters for the exclusive use
13 of either females or males.
14 2. Every restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters within a
15 covered entity that is designated for use by females or males shall
16 only be used by members of the designated sex. No individual shall
17 enter a restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters that is
18 designated for members of the opposite sex.
19 3. A covered entity shall take reasonable steps to provide
20 individuals with privacy from members of the opposite sex in
21 restrooms, changing rooms, and sleeping quarters.
22 4. This section shall not apply to an individual who enters a
23 restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters designated for members
24 of the opposite sex in any of the following circumstances:
SB418 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 a. performance of custodial services or maintenance,
2 b. rendering of medical or law enforcement assistance, or
3 c. provision of services or aid during a natural disaster
4 or declared emergency, or when necessary to prevent a
5 serious threat to order and safety.
6 5. Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit a
7 covered entity from:
8 a. adopting policies necessary to accommodate persons
9 protected under the Americans with Disabilities Act of
10 1990 or elderly persons in need of aid or assistance,
11 b. establishing single-occupancy restrooms, changing
12 rooms, or sleeping quarters, or
13 c. redesignating a multi-occupancy restroom, changing
14 room, or sleeping quarters designated for exclusive
15 use by members of one sex to that of members of the
16 opposite sex.
17 6. The Department of Corrections shall promulgate rules to
18 administer the provisions of this section.
19 C. 1. Any individual who accesses a restroom or changing room
20 for use by members of his or her sex and encounters a person of the
21 opposite sex in such restroom or changing room has a private cause
22 of action for declaratory and injunctive relief against the covered
23 entity that:
24
