1 a. provided permission to the person of the opposite sex
2 to use such restroom or changing room, or
3 b. failed to take reasonable steps to prohibit access of
4 the restroom or changing room to the person of the
5 opposite sex.
6 2. Any individual who is required by the covered entity to
7 share sleeping quarters with a person of the opposite sex has a
8 private cause of action for declaratory and injunctive relief
9 against the covered entity.
10 3. Any civil action brought against a covered entity pursuant
11 to this section shall be initiated within two (2) years after the
12 violation occurred. Any individual aggrieved pursuant to this
13 section who prevails in court may recover reasonable attorney fees
14 and court costs from the covered entity.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
